brewery.brewery_description:
Central District Brewing is an urban small batch brewery in the heart of Downtown Austin that crafts durable friendship along with mainstays, seasonal, and experimental beers and sodas.

Founded in 2019 by two families who wanted to bring back beer brewing to downtown Austin (following the likes of The Bitter End, Waterloo, Coppertank, and Lovejoy’s), we were honored to win a 2019 GABF gold medal for our WIT-tington.

beer.beer_description: New Collab Magic! Behold, the Megalomaniac Rye DIPA (8.5%)! In cahoots with our pals at @middletonbrewing, we've concocted a brew that's pure alchemy – a dank West Coast-style DIPA with a mischievous twist of rye. This potion is spicy, sublime, and oh-so-balancing! Get ready to embark on a flavor adventure.

beer.beer_description:
NEW SCHOOL IPA
West Coastie w/ citrus and a hint of pine. (Citra, Mosaic, El Dorado)
Clean and crisp with delicate fruit aromas
Sometimes getting the “short straw” is a good thing, especially when it’s in the form of good beer. Forward notes of roasted coffee, smooth chocolate, with touches of toffee and caramel.

NEW SCHOOL IPA
West Coastie w/ citrus and a hint of pine. (Citra, Mosaic, El Dorado)
Aromas of spice, clove, and banana with the essence of fresh baked bread, raisins, and October.
Hazy IPA: Notes of orange zest, grapefruit, and marmalade.

Introducing: The Saint of Lost Causes, our Belgian quadrupel.

As the seasons change, styles of beer change with them, and with that in mind (and heart, honestly), we present a 10.3% ABV Belgian quad that runs deep with strong flavors of plum and fig, toffee, molasses, and chocolate covered cherry.

Much akin to a folk song, one like this beer is named after, don’t let the sweetness deceive you. This one is after your soul. ?

On the tap wall now. Come get yourself a pour and see why it’s one of the new staff favorites.

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy

beer.beer_description: IPA brewed with a Norwegian Kviek yeast

INTRODUCING: Texas Skies, our American IPA — A bit like jumping into the river after a long hike through the Texas pines, this, dare we say, perfectly balanced IPA is sure to hit all the right notes when and where you need it most. Simcoe and Mosaic keep it real and nostalgic; Rakau nudges it towards new school. 6.8% ABV. Come have a pint and see why the brew team is so stoked about it.
Milkshake IPA w/ Peaches & Vanilla
Fleshy peach, bright tangerine, loads of ripe apricot and soft approachable bitterness
Double dry hopped DIPA with Sabro, El Dorado and Rakau.
Characteristically dry & complex with subtle citrus, pear & candied fruit notes.
Citrus twist to the classic West Coast pine. (Mosaic, El Dorado)

Concentric Circles (7.1% West Coast Hazy IPA). We are in a jazzy sort of mood today with this overcast weather. This beer is sure to keep you dry with its brut finish. Action packed hop bill of Citra, Azacca, NZ Rakau, Simcoe-cryo, and BRU-1 leads an intense pineapple and tropical fruit nose followed by a dry, piney, grapefruit body.

New Collab Magic! Behold, the Megalomaniac Rye DIPA (8.5%)! In cahoots with our pals at @middletonbrewing, we've concocted a brew that's pure alchemy – a dank West Coast-style DIPA with a mischievous twist of rye. This potion is spicy, sublime, and oh-so-balancing! Get ready to embark on a flavor adventure.
Crisp German malt aroma complemented with delicate honey & biscuit notes
Refreshing coconut & ripe pineapple aromas w/ refined juicy bitterness
